Former Congressman and Secretary of the Interior Stewart Udall has passed away. President Obama issued a statement acknowledging Udall's honorable service to the nation, both in the military and in his various roles in government. Udall's dedication to environmental causes, including clean air and water, as well as the preservation of natural treasures, has left a lasting impact on the country. The President expressed condolences to the Udall family, who continue to carry on his legacy of public service.